    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third-party holding account where funds and documents are kept safe until all conditions of the deal are met, ensuring neither you nor the seller can be scammed or cheated. You need it because Toronto real estate transactions are complex, involving multiple agents, lawyers, and strict timing, so the escrow agent acts as a watchdog to verify that the seller's title is clean, the mortgage is approved, and the inspection reports are satisfactory before the keys are handed over. Without this protective layer, you would be risking your entire down payment on a house that might have hidden issues or legal disputes, which is exactly why the Toronto Real Estate Board mandates it for every closing.\n\nThink of it like a secure vault that only releases the money to the seller once the deed is officially transferred and the buyer has the right to take possession. If you skipped escrow, it would be like handing over your life savings directly to a stranger without checking their ID or verifying their story, which is why a professional escrow agent is essential for your peace of mind. You can rest easy knowing that the escrow officer is meticulously checking every document and ensuring the transaction follows all Ontario laws before the final signature is put on the line.",
