    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so basically someone else just holds the money so nobody gets ripped off. who exactly is the person or company that usually manages this? is it just a bank or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In Toronto, the escrow agent is usually a specialized real estate lawyer or a specific escrow company, not just a standard bank branch. While some banks offer escrow services as an add-on, most transactions in the Greater Toronto Area are handled by legal professionals who are licensed to close deals under the Ontario Real Estate Act. They act as the neutral third party, holding the funds and managing the paperwork until every last detail is perfect.\n\nIt's important to know that you can't just pick any random lawyer for this; they need to be registered with the Law Society of Ontario and often work with the specific real estate board in your area. This ensures that the escrow officer knows all the local rules and regulations that apply to your specific purchase. If the process isn't handled by a qualified professional, you risk having your funds frozen or the deal falling through for months, which is why the market relies on these experts to keep things moving smoothly.\n\nBasically, think of the escrow agent as the ultimate referee who ensures the game of buying a house is played fairly according to the rulebook. They are the ones who physically receive your money from the bank and then distribute it to the seller, the builder, or the government once the final conditions",
      "source": "target",
